  "text": ", where s 0 is the phosphorescent lifetime in the absence of oxygen and k q is the quenching constant. The k q value of 222 mmHg -1 s -1 was used as this value corresponds to a temperature of 27°C, the average temperature of the dorsal window chamber skin during imaging. [CITATION_1] The value of s 0 was determined to be 243 ms under our experimental conditions using a solution of Oxyphor G4 into which nitrogen gas was bubbled for 20 min.",
